{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἅπᾱς</b>, ἅπᾱσα <br /> (also ἅπανσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 56.25 (Argos, 5th c.BC))\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], ἅπαν (ἅ- = <b>sṃ-,</b> compare εἷς), strengthened for πᾶς, <b>quite all, the whole,</b> and in <i>plural</i> <b>all together,</b> frequently from [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus downwards; ἅπασι \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<b>in all things,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.1; τοῖσι ἅπασι 91; ἐν ἅπασι 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Κωακαὶ προγνώσιες” 156; ἐφ᾽ ἅπασι 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.365. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> with <i>adjective</i>, ἀργύρεος δὲ ἔστιν ἅ. <b>all</b> silver, i.e. of <b>massive</b> silver, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.616, 15.116; ἅ. δὲ τραχὺς ὅστις ἂν νέον κρατῇ 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 35; μικκός γα μᾶκος.. ἀλλ᾽ ἅπαν κακόν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 909, compare 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.19, 148\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ ἐναντία ἅπασα ὁδός the <b>exactly</b> contrary way, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 317b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> with abstract <i>substantive</i>, <b>all possible, absolute,</b> ἅπασ᾽ ἀνάγκη[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 171; σπουδή 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 6.23; ἀτοπία 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 39.1.7; εἰς ἅπαν ἀφικέσθαι ἀνοίας 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 7.15.8. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> sometimes with <i>Article</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.64, +others, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 483, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.13. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> after [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] in <i>singular</i>, <b>every one,</b> <i>neuter</i> <b>everything,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 108b\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ πρὸς [τοῦ] ἅπαντος ἀνδρός not in the power of <b>every</b> man, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.153; οὐκ ἐξ ἅπαντος δεῖ τὸ κερδαίνειν φιλεῖν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 312\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐξἅπαντος εὖ λέγει <b>in any cause whatever,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “OC” 807; σῖγα νῦν ἅπας ἔχε σίγαν 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 144\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἅπαν γένοιτ᾽ ἂν ἤδη <b>nihil non..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 528\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>substantive</i>, ἅπαντι λόγῳ in <b>every</b> matter, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 231\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ ἅπαν, as <i>adverb</i>, <b>altogether,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 241b\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; καθ᾽ ἅπαν as <b>a whole,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-4th c.BC: Timaeus Locrus Philosophus 96d; ἐς ἅπαν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.103; εἰς ἅπαν \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>at all,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Libanius Sophista “Orationes” 18.266; πρὸς ἅπαν 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.493; ἐξ ἅπαντος 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Merc.Cond.” 41. [ᾰπᾰν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.185, etc., 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 2.49\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; but ᾰπᾱν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 129, 4th c.AD: Metrodorus Epigrammaticus 57, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 2.56, and _Attic dialect_ _accusative_ to Hdn.Gr. 2.12\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ᾰπᾰν in <i>anapaest meter</i>, [<a 